title: Service Level Agreement
content: This document outlines the service level agreement between Dash and our vendor partners. Key metrics include: 99.9% uptime guarantee, 4-hour response time for critical issues, monthly performance reviews. The agreement covers data processing, security requirements, and compliance obligations. Effective date: January 1, 2024. Renewal: Annual review required.

title: Data Handling Procedures
content: Vendor data handling procedures and security requirements. All vendor personnel must complete security training before accessing Dash systems. Data classification levels: Public, Internal, Confidential, Regulated. Access controls: Role-based permissions, regular access reviews, audit logging required. Incident reporting: Contact security@dash.com within 1 hour of discovery.

title: Q1 2024 Quarterly Review
content: Quarterly business review meeting notes. Attendees: Dash leadership team, vendor representatives. Topics discussed: Performance metrics, upcoming projects, budget planning, risk assessment. Key decisions: Increase vendor capacity by 20%, implement new security protocols, schedule next review for April 2024. Action items: Update contracts, conduct security training, prepare Q2 budget proposal.
